{
  "texts": [
    "After doing this for each message bit, we concatenate the selected string to get a signature.",
    "• When a user (who already knows the public key (pk 0, pk 1) receives the message M and the signa- ture, she can easily verify the signature.",
    "We represent the i-th component of the signature as s i, and the user can examine the corresponding message M i and calculate the hash value H(s i).",
    "If M i = 0, the hash must match the elements in the public key pk 0; If M i = 1, the hash must match the elements in public key pk 1.",
    "If each element in the signature is hashed to find the corresponding public key for the correct part, we say that the signature is valid."
  ]
}